body.description: The instinctive action of sucking helps to calm and soothe babies and all parents know theres nothing more wonderful than a calm, content baby. When moms breast isnt available, our Breast-like pacifier is the next best thing for baby to latch onto in between feeds. This pacifier glows in the dark for up to 8 hours which allows parents to locate the pacifier in a dark room without having to disturb baby. During the day your pacifier will recharge in natural light.Inspired by our award-winning Closer to Nature nipple, this super soft silicone pacifier feels, moves, flexes and stretches just like skin so theres less chance of confusion when feeding baby from breast or bottle - perfect if youre worried that offering your baby a pacifier may disrupt breast or bottle feeding. As the symmetrical silicone baglet is fully reversible, there is no wrong side-up so the pacifier will always be placed correctly in your babys mouth, even when they put it in their mouth themselves. The pacifier shield curves away from babys face and offers superior ventilation and extra air flow and prevent the build-up of moisture which helps to protect babys delicate skin against irritation.We recommend that you replace the pacifier every month and always at the first signs of damage or weakness. We recommend stopping pacifier use when your child is older than 36 months.*as compared to traditional round unvented pacifiers which do not compress as easily.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Natural soothing experience Babies will naturally look to mom for comfort. When mom’s breast isn’t available, the Tommee Tippee Breast-like pacifier is the next best thing for baby to latch onto in between feeds. Taking inspiration from Mother Nature and our Closer to Nature nipple, this super soft silicone pacifier feels, moves, flexes and stretches just like skin so there’s less chance of confusion when feeding baby from breast or bottle - perfect if you’re worried that offering your baby a pacifier may disrupt breast or bottle feeding.

Symmetrical design The symmetrical, soft silicone baglet is fully reversible and has no ‘wrong-side-up’ so the pacifier will always be placed correctly in your baby’s mouth, even when baby puts the pacifier in their mouth themselves. Kind to baby’s skin Sucking and dribbling can sometimes mean baby’s skin becomes irritated around the mouth. The Tommee Tippee Breast-like pacifier curves away from baby’s face and offers superior ventilation to increase airflow and prevent rashes. Glow in the dark The Breast-like pacifier Night glows in the dark for up to 8 hours, so when your baby launches it from their cot in the middle of the night, it’s really easy to spot! During the day your pacifier will recharge in natural light, the more light the longer the glow, it’s as easy as that.

Available in different age stages The Breast-like night pacifier is suitable for use from birth and is available in two age stages. The 0-6-month size features a smaller nipple and shield for tiny mouths and noses. As your baby grows, you can switch to the 6-18m pacifier which offers the same benefits but with a larger nipple and shield. Easy to clean & BPA-free Silicone is taste-free and won’t retain any stains or odors. Easy to clean either in a sterilizer, by hand or in the top rack of the dishwasher. Always BPA and phthalate-free for your ultimate reassurance. How often should I replace my baby’s pacifier? In the interests of hygiene, we recommend that you change your baby’s pacifier every month. Always check the pacifier before each use and replace at the first signs of damage or weakness. We recommend against prolonged pacifier use over 24 months and stopping pacifier use when your child is older than 36 months.

reviews.reviewText: We only got to use these for a few weeks before our baby stopped taking pacifiers, but they were awesome. She had a hard time spitting these out which was nice to keep her latched. The glow in the dark was a nice touch for night feedings as well

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: A good shape - no issues switching from breast to bottle
reviews.reviewText: These are really good dummies which I used for the first 8 weeks. I was worried about the use of a dummy and nipple rejection with breast feeding. These work well and we could switch between the two no problem. We used them in conjunction with the bottle with the same shape and my 3 month old has never rejected the bottle. These have an excellent glow in the dark feature which allow you to easily be able to spot a dummy which has fallen out (equally good when trying to settle in a darkened room).
Ottimo per neonati in allattamento, se non riuscite a trovare il ciuccio che soddisfi il vostro bimbo questo può essere la soluzione
Buon prodotto e buon prezzo rispetto ai negozi fisici, ma mia figlia, con la quale ho provato diversi tipi e forme, non li ha accettati.

reviews.reviewText: Bought these for my LO to try out as we have the bottles and I breast feed. Didn’t cause any nipple confusion like the other dummy brands however my LO just doesn’t seem to be a dummy guy and would much rather use me as one!They were white and blue but do not glow in the dark
